Note for users: this software is indicative of the published works based on
the PhD thesis "Towards Computationally Scalable Inter-Reconfigurable Robots"
(Ash Wan Yaw Sang, 2025, SUTD). Two additional works from the same thesis are
currently under review and will be shared upon their respective publication.
The Glasius Bioinspired Neural Network (GBNN) reference implementation in
`replicated_gbnn.py` is a re-implementation of prior work by Glasius, Komoda,
& Gielen (1995). The A* algorithm (Hart, Nilsson, & Raphael, 1968) and
Dijkstra's algorithm (Dijkstra, 1959) are included as base path-planning
functions used to demonstrate deployed inter-reconfigurable robots. Credit
for these classical algorithms belongs to their original authors.
